ile hydrothermal acetaldehyde diversification supplies isobutyraldehyde; these converge in the classical valine aminonitrile route.", "reaction_sequence": ["rxn_004", "rxn_003", "rxn_006", "rxn_007", "rxn_008"], "key_intermediates": ["mol_004", "mol_009", "mol_011"]}, {"pathway_id": "P4", "name": "Formamide-assisted Strecker preservation route", "description": "HCN first accesses formamide-rich surface chemistry, supporting aminonitrile persistence, then the standard Strecker sequence proceeds from isobutyraldehyde to valine.", "reaction_sequence": ["rxn_004", "rxn_005", "rxn_003", "rxn_006", "rxn_007", "rxn_008"], "key_intermediates": ["mol_004", "mol_013", "mol_011"]}, {"pathway_id": "P5", "name": "Bucherer-Bergs bridge from branched aldehyde to alpha-ketoisovalerate then valine", "description": "Trace isobutyraldehyde enters a CO2-containing Bucherer-Bergs-like manifold producing hydantoin-linked intermediates and a keto-acid branch, then reductive amination yields valine.", "reaction_sequence": ["rxn_003", "rxn_006", "rxn_009", "rxn_011"], "key_intermediates": ["mol_009", "mol_014", "mol_010"]}, {"pathway_id": "P6", "name": "Hydrothermal keto-acid route from pyruvate", "description": "Hydrothermal formate reduction feeds pyruvate, pyruvate and acetaldehyde enter a speculative protometabolic condensation to alpha-ketoisovalerate, and hydrothermal reductive amination furnishes valine.", "reaction_sequence": ["rxn_001", "rxn_002", "rxn_003", "rxn_010", "rxn_011"], "key_intermediates": ["mol_005", "mol_008", "mol_010"]}, {"pathway_id": "P7", "name": "Pyruvate-centered metabolically congruent route", "description": "A pyruvate hub formed in hydrothermal settings is funneled into alpha-ketoisovalerate in concentrated prebiotic pools and then reduced to valine on iron-sulfur minerals.", "reaction_sequence": ["rxn_002", "rxn_010", "rxn_011"], "key_intermediates": ["mol_008", "mol_010"]}, {"pathway_id": "P8", "name": "Convergent HCN and alpha-keto acid dual-entry route", "description": "One branch forms valine aminonitrile by Strecker chemistry while another independently forms alpha-ketoisovalerate; both converge on the same target through hydrolysis or reductive amination.", "reaction_sequence": ["rxn_004", "rxn_003", "rxn_006", "rxn_007", "rxn_008", "rxn_002", "rxn_010", "rxn_011"], "key_intermediates": ["mol_004", "mol_011", "mol_010"]}, {"pathway_id": "P9", "name": "Bottleneck-explicit branched aldehyde route", "description": "This pathway isolates the key literature bottleneck: low-yield surface formation of isobutyraldehyde from acetaldehyde, followed by the validated Strecker chemistry to valine.", "reaction_sequence": ["rxn_006", "rxn_007", "rxn_008"], "key_intermediates": ["mol_009", "mol_011"]}, {"pathway_id": "P10", "name": "Integrated hydrothermal-surface-biochemical network route", "description": "Hydrothermal CO2 reduction produces reduced carbon hubs; surface photochemistry produces HCN and concentration; hydrothermal and surface branches jointly feed both Strecker and keto-acid channels to valine.", "reaction_sequence": ["rxn_001", "rxn_003", "rxn_004", "rxn_006", "rxn_007", "rxn_008", "rxn_002", "rxn_010", "rxn_011"], "key_intermediates": ["mol_005", "mol_007", "mol_004", "mol_009", "mol_010", "mol_011"]}], "hub_molecules": ["mol_004", "mol_007", "mol_008", "mol_009", "mol_010", "mol_011"], "convergence_points": [{"molecule_id": "mol_009", "incoming_reactions": ["rxn_006"], "outgoing_reactions": ["rxn_007", "rxn_009"]}, {"molecule_id": "mol_010", "incoming_reactions": ["rxn_009", "rxn_010", "rxn_012"], "outgoing_reactions": ["rxn_011", "rxn_012"]}, {"molecule_id": "mol_011", "incoming_reactions": ["rxn_007"], "outgoing_reactions": ["rxn_008"]}, {"molecule_id": "mol_007", "incoming_reactions": ["rxn_003"], "outgoing_reactions": ["rxn_006", "rxn_010"]}, {"molecule_id": "mol_008", "incoming_reactions": ["rxn_002"], "outgoing_reactions": ["rxn_010"]}]}, "reasoning": "", "duration_ms": 108266.15118980408, "success": tr